Did Bella Hadid and The Weeknd just make things official via Instagram? Not long ago one of the supermodel sisters Gigi Hadid confirmed she had revived her romance with Zayn Malik, and now Bella has reportedly reunited with the Worth It singer The Weeknd. After several meetings together over the summer, most notably at the Cannes Film Festival in May, where they were spotted looking very cosy in each other’s company. Now the duo enjoyed a weekend of partying with friends in Tokyo. Abel Tesfaye posted an Instagram Story of the supermodel model laughing as the group checked out Tokyo’s famous Robot Restaurant.  Afterwards, they headed to a karaoke bar, singing along to hits like N.E.R.D’s Everyone Nose (All the Girls Standing in the Line for the Bathroom) and Britney Spears’ Lucky. #bellahadid & @fannybourdettedonon A post shared by  Bella Hadid (@bellahnews) on Jul 22, 2018 at 9:46am PDT  The Starboy singer shared a photo of himself with two of his friends in the frenetic Japanese capital, making sure to credit the photographer – @bellahadid. No More Dreams  : @bellahadid A post shared by  The Weeknd (@theweeknd) on Jul 22, 2018 at 7:12am PDT 